<h1>How to Update Dashboard Data &mdash; Quick Reference Card</h1>

<p>A concise reference for updating all four WSU Facilities Services dashboards. For detailed walkthroughs, see the individual guides listed at the end of this document.</p>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>1. Dashboard Overview</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<table>
<tr><th>Dashboard</th><th>URL</th><th>Data Source</th><th>Update Frequency</th></tr>
<tr>
  <td>Energy Cost Projection</td>
  <td>jswsu.github.io/wsu-energy-dashboard/</td>
  <td>Excel VBA macro &rarr; data.json</td>
  <td>Monthly (after Kintec/Avista bills)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Campus Metering</td>
  <td>jswsu.github.io/wsu-energy-dashboard/metering.html</td>
  <td>SkySpark &rarr; 7 JSON files</td>
  <td>Monthly</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Water Conservation</td>
  <td>jswsu.github.io/wsu-energy-dashboard/water-conservation.html</td>
  <td>Same as Metering (shared data files)</td>
  <td>Monthly (before meeting)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Steam Plant Operations</td>
  <td>jswsu.github.io/wsu-energy-dashboard/steam-plant.html</td>
  <td>Excel import via dashboard</td>
  <td>Monthly (after Energy Report)</td>
</tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>2. All Dashboards</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<table>
<tr><th>Item</th><th>Details</th></tr>
<tr><td>Password</td><td><b>Energy@WSU</b> &mdash; same for all four dashboards</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dark mode</td><td>Toggle in the header bar; preference saved in browser</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deployment</td><td>GitHub Pages auto-deploys within 1&ndash;2 minutes of any push to the <code>main</code> branch</td></tr>
<tr><td>Browser refresh</td><td>After pushing new data, hard refresh with <b>Ctrl+Shift+R</b> to bypass cache</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>3. Energy Cost Projection Update</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 1.</span> Open the Energy Report Excel workbook on the shared drive (R:\ENERGY GROUP\...Energy Report\).</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 2.</span> Enter the latest monthly data, then run the <b>Export to JSON</b> VBA macro. Review the verification message for any warnings.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 3.</span> Copy the exported <code>data.json</code> file to the root of the Git repo.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 4.</span> Commit and push to GitHub (or upload <code>data.json</code> directly via the GitHub web interface).</div>

<div class="tip"><span class="tip-label">Tip:</span> The VBA macro cross-checks exported values against the consolidated data sheet and flags discrepancies greater than 5%.</div>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>4. Campus Metering / Water Conservation Update</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 1.</span> In SkySpark Shell, run: <code>task_exportToIO(2025-01-01..2026-03-31)</code> &mdash; adjust the end date to the current month.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 2.</span> Open the SkySpark <b>Files</b> app &rarr; <code>io/</code> folder. Download all 7 JSON files to your local machine.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 3.</span> Run <code>push-data.sh</code> from Git Bash, or manually upload the files to the <code>data/</code> folder on GitHub.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 4.</span> Hard refresh the dashboard (<b>Ctrl+Shift+R</b>) to verify the new data appears.</div>

<div class="tip"><span class="tip-label">Tip:</span> Both the Metering and Water Conservation dashboards share <code>domestic_water.json</code> and <code>irrigation.json</code>, so one update covers both.</div>

<table>
<tr><th>Export File</th><th>Used By</th></tr>
<tr><td>electric.json</td><td>Metering</td></tr>
<tr><td>condensate.json</td><td>Metering</td></tr>
<tr><td>chw.json</td><td>Metering</td></tr>
<tr><td>domestic_water.json</td><td>Metering + Water Conservation</td></tr>
<tr><td>irrigation.json</td><td>Metering + Water Conservation</td></tr>
<tr><td>sites.json</td><td>Metering</td></tr>
<tr><td>connectors.json</td><td>Metering</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>5. Steam Plant Operations Update</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 1.</span> Open the Steam Plant Operations dashboard &rarr; navigate to the <b>Data Management</b> tab.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 2.</span> Drag and drop the monthly Energy Report Excel file onto the upload area.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 3.</span> Review the parsed data preview, then click <b>Merge Into Dataset</b>.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 4.</span> Click <b>Download JSON</b> to save the updated dataset, then upload it to the <code>data/</code> folder on GitHub.</div>

<div class="tip"><span class="tip-label">Tip:</span> The dashboard validates and previews data before merging, so you can catch errors before committing.</div>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<h2>6. UP Report Generation</h2>
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 1.</span> Open the Steam Plant Operations dashboard &rarr; navigate to the <b>UP Report</b> tab.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 2.</span> Select the target month from the dropdown and click <b>Load Data</b>.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 3.</span> Enter the manual fields from Kintec/Avista invoices (costs, delivery charges, etc.).</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 4.</span> Click <b>Generate UP Report Excel</b> to produce the formatted spreadsheet.</div>
<div class="step"><span class="step-num">Step 5.</span> Save the generated file to the shared drive: <code>R:\ENERGY GROUP\...\UP\UP2026\</code></div>

<div class="warning"><b>Important:</b> Double-check all manually entered invoice values before generating. The report is used for official university utility billing.</div>

